<HEADLINE> 3 Killed in Traffic Accident in France </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, April 25 (Xinhua) -- Three people were killed and nine
others injured in a pile-up of six cars on an expressway in the
Loire region in central France, reported Agence France-Presse
(AFP).
</P>
<P>
AFP quoted police as saying that the incident took place around
four o'clock in the afternoon near Loir-et-Cher on one single lane
of the expressway linking Paris with the province.
</P>
<P>
No further details about the incident were provided. 
</P>
</TEXT>
