<HEADLINE> Fire in E. Tanzania Burns Sisal Twine, Clothes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, April 25 (Xinhua) -- A fire in east Tanzania's
Tanga Municipality has burnt 42 bales of sisal twine and second
hand clothes into ashes, according to a report reaching here
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The fire, which broke out early this week, has destroyed goods
worth 4.3 million Shillings (about 6,500 US dollars), Andrew
Mkuzi, the owner, told reporters Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Mkuzi blamed the Tanga Municipality fire brigade who came to
the scene 45 minutes later after he telephoned them. He said the
fire brigade officials claimed that they were facing water
shortage and went back, leaving the fire raging.
</P>
<P>
The fire, believed to be caused by an electrical fault, was
put off by the Tanzania Harbors Authority (THA) fire department.
</P>
<P>
The emergency crew of State Power Company later arrived and
disconnected the fault line in the store.  
</P>
</TEXT>
