<HEADLINE> Ethiopian Birr Devalued to 7.001 Against US </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, April 25 (Xinhua) -- The Ethiopian Birr is
devalued to 7.001 against US Dollar beginning from Monday, the
lowest level against the dollar since the currency was devalued
in 1992.
</P>
<P>
According to an announcement made by the National Bank of
Ethiopia on Saturday, with effect from April 27 until May 3,
1998, the marginal exchange rate for one US Dollar is 7.001 Birr.
</P>
<P>
The announcement was made after weekly foreign exchange
auction held here Saturday morning. The bank said on the auction
that the highest bid rate was 7.231 whereas the lowest was 6.957
for one US Dollar.
</P>
<P>
The total amount of foreign exchange made available at the
auction was 17 million dollars, and bidders who offered rates of
7.001 Birr and above for one US Dollar won the full amount they
tendered for.
</P>
<P>
The Birr was devalued from 2.07 to 5 Birr to the dollar in
1992, a level at which it was pegged for more than 25 years.
</P>
<P>
Ethiopia introduced foreign exchange auction system in May, 1993.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
