<HEADLINE> Afghan General Dostam Visits Iran </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, April 25 (Xinhua) -- Leader of Afghan National Islamic
Movement (NIM) General Abdul Rashid Dostam arrived here Saturday
evening for discussions with Iranian leaders on Afghan situation.
</P>
<P>
Dostam, the top military commander in northern Afghanistan, is
expected to hold meetings with the Iranian Foreign Minister Kamal
Kharrazi, special envoy in Afghan affairs Alaeddin Boroujerdi and
other Iranian officials.
</P>
<P>
He may also confer with Iranian President Mohammad Khatami,
according to the Iranian official news agency IRNA.
</P>
<P>
Dostam's visit is considered as important since it came on the
threshold of the peace talks in Pakistan between the
representatives of the Afghan Taliban militia and the rival
Northern Alliance led by Afghan President Burhanuddin Rabbani.
</P>
<P>
Dostam, a former general of the Uzbek militia which supported
the former pro-Soviet government, turned to back Rabbani after the
Taliban forces drew his government out of the Afghan capital Kabul
in September 1996.
</P>
<P>
Following the recent visit of the U.S. ambassador to the
United Nations Bill Richardson to Afghanistan, both the Taliban
and the Northern Alliance agreed to hold peace talks to put an end
to the Afghan civil war since 1992 after the Muslims Jihad groups
ousted former pro-Soviet government. 
</P>
</TEXT>
