<BODY>
<HEADLINE> High-Speed Hovercraft Launched in Guangdong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, April 26 (Xinhua) -- A new high-speed catamaran-type
hovercraft developed independently by China was launched today in
the Nansha Development Zone in Fanyu City, Guangdong Province, to
transport passengers between Hong Kong and Nansha.
</P>
<P>
The vessel has a designed maximum speed of 48 knots. It was
constructed by the Nansha Xinji Shipyard in accordance with both
the regulations of the International Maritime Organization (IMO)
and the China Classification Society (CCS).
</P>
<P>
The ship also has advanced telecommunications and navigation
equipment such as global positioning systems and radar. It is
driven by four engines totalling 10,000 hp and four water-jet
propellers.
</P>
<P>
Henry Ying-Tung Fok, vice-chairman of the National Committee of
the Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference, attended
the launching ceremony.  
</P>
