<HEADLINE> Statue of Movie Star Unveiled in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 26 (Xinhua) -- A statue of Ruan Lingyu, a
leading Chinese female movie star (1909-1935) in the 1920s and
1930s, was unveiled in Fushouyuan Cemetery here today, on the 80th
anniversary of her birth.
</P>
<P>
One of the earliest Chinese film actresses, Ruan starred in 29
movies. Her representative work, "Goddess", marked the height of
the development of China's film industry in the 1930s.
</P>
<P>
Ruan committed suicide following controversy surrounding her
role in "New Female" in 1935, when she was just 26 years old.
</P>
<P>
About 100,000 Shanghai residents took part in her funeral
procession.
</P>
<P>
A picture exhibition about Ruan's life was also held in
Shanghai today.  
</P>
</TEXT>
