<HEADLINE> Chongqing to Host Assets Restructuring Fair </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, April 26 (Xinhua) -- A fair on assets restructuring
is scheduled to be held in this southwestern China metropolis May
14-15.
</P>
<P>
More than 1,000 enterprises from 24 major cities along the
Yangtze River, including the cities of Shanghai, Nanjing, Wuhan
and Chongqing, will participate this regional fair, the biggest of
its kind ever, according to Xiao Jiankang, a Chongqing municipal
government official in charge of economic restructuring work.
</P>
<P>
A property exchange market network has so far taken shape
in the Yangtze River Valley, known as China's "Golden Economic
Region" for its rapid economic growth rate.
</P>
<P>
The fair is expected to expand and standardize the activities
of property exchange and assets restructuring among the provinces
in the valley and boost their economic cooperation, Xiao said.
