<HEADLINE> NPC Mulls Five Draft Laws </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 26 (Xinhua) -- China's top legislative body
today convened to deliberate five draft laws, including amendments
to the Forestry Law and the Law on Fire Control.
</P>
<P>
Li Peng, chairman of the Standing Committee of the National
People's Congress (NPC), presided over the inaugural meeting of
NPC Standing Committee's second session, which will last four days.
</P>
<P>
Li Boyong and Zhou Keyu, vice-chairmen of the NPC Law
Committee, delivered speeches on the drafts of amendments to
the Forestry Law and Law on Fire Control, respectively.
</P>
<P>
Qiao Xiaoyang, also an NPC Law Committee vice-chairman,
reported to the meeting about amendments to the draft of the Law on
Higher Education.
</P>
<P>
Minister of Land and Natural Resources Zhou Yongkang explained
amendments to the draft of the Land-Use Law.
</P>
<P>
Hou Zongbin, chairman of the NPC Committee for Internal and
Judicial Affairs, explained the draft of the law on the prevention of
juvenile delinquency.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Deguang, vice-minister of foreign affairs, explained
the proposal for a judicial assistance treaty between China and
Uzbekistan.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the session also examined a name list of the
proposed members of the Preparatory Committee of the Macao Special
Administrative Region. 
</P>
