<HEADLINE> Anton and McKiernan Win London Marathon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, April 26 (Xinhua) -- World champion Abel Anton of Spain
took the London marathon men's race in two hours seven minutes and
56 seconds by holding off Moroccan Abdelkar El Mouaziz on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Ireland's Catherina McKiernan won the women's race after
leading for the final five miles in her second ever marathon race
with a time of 2:26:25.
</P>
<P>
Pre-race predictions that the men's world record would go
proved wide of the mark, but Anton was just two seconds outside
the course record.
</P>
<P>
El Mouaziz, who had led for much of the second half of the
race, held on for second place in 2:08:07, ahead of last year's
winner Antonio Pinto of Portugal, who was third in 2:08:13
</P>
<P>
In the women's, McKiernan finished the 26 miles with almost
half a minute clear of Britain's Liz McColgan, who finished second
in 2:26:54
</P>
<P>
Defending champion Joyce Chepchumba of South Africa was third
in 2:27:22. China's Wang Yanfang finished eighth in 2:30:47.
</P>
<P>
The 28-year-old McKiernan, four-times world cross-country
runner-up, broke away from the pack on 19 miles, surging past the
early surprise leader Adriana Fernandez of Mexico. 
</P>
</TEXT>
