<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-26 12:33 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Khatami Calls for Islamic Unity Against Israel </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, April 26 (Xinhua) -- Iranian President Mohammad
Khatami on Sunday urged the Islamic countries to be united, rally
around their common interests and promote understanding among
themselves in order to face the Israeli challenges.
</P>
<P>
In his meeting with visiting Syrian First Vice President
Abdul-Halim Khaddam, Khatami also called for further promotion of
cooperation among Islamic countries within the framework of the
Organization of the Islamic Conference (OIC) and the United
Nations.
</P>
<P>
According to the Iranian official news agency IRNA, Khaddam
handed Khatami a letter from Syrian President Hafez al-Assad,
who invited his Iranian counterpart to visit Damascus. However, no
detailed content of the letter was revealed.
</P>
<P>
Khaddam also briefed the Iranian president on the latest
regional developments and the recent Israeli plan of conditional
withdrawal from south Lebanon. He called on Muslim countries to
join hands in solving problems facing the world of Islam.
</P>
<P>
Israel decided on April 1 to accept the U.N. Resolution 425,
which calls for an unconditional Israeli withdrawal from south
Lebanon. But meanwhile, Israel said it would not exit unless
security arrangements for its northern border areas are worked out
with the Lebanese government.
</P>
<P>
Khaddam arrived here Saturday afternoon and held two rounds of
talks with his Iranian counterpart Hassan Habibi. He concluded
his visit to Iran and left here for Damascus Sunday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Before his departure, Khaddam said that he is satisfied with
his visit to Tehran, adding that during the meetings held between
the two countries' officials, Iran and Syria shared common
viewpoints on different issues which will be announced in a joint
communique later on.
</P>
<P>
Referring to the critical situation in Iraq, he noted that
Syria underlines the need to maintain territorial integrity of
Iraq and is opposed to any military action against it.
</P>
<P>
Habibi, seeing Khaddam off at the airport, called for
implementation of the U.N. Resolution 425, saying that Iran
supports the stance of Syria and Lebanon that rejects any
condition for withdrawal of the Israeli forces from south
Lebanon. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
