<HEADLINE> Macao SAR Preparatory Committee to Be Set up in May </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 26 (Xinhua) -- The Preparatory Committee of the
Macao Special Administrative Region (SAR) will be established in
May, with its headquarters here in the capital of China.
</P>
<P>
This is in accordance with a resolution made at the first
session of the Eighth National People's Congress (NPC) in
1993. The preparatory committee will be in charge of affairs
related to the region.
</P>
<P>
After repeated study and consultation, the NPC chairmen's
meeting today submitted a 100-member name list of the preparatory
committee to the ongoing second session of the Ninth NPC standing
commitee, including 40 from China's interior areas and 60 from
Macao.
</P>
<P>
Most of the members from interior areas are government
officials and scholars who are more involved with Macao's affairs.
</P>
<P>
The Macao members include politicians, business people,
workers, social workers and people from religious circles.
</P>
<P>
The committee will make preparations for the future
administration of the region and formulate rules for the
election of its first chief executive, its first legislative
council and the judicial authorities.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, it will make preparations for the ceremony marking
the return of Macao to the motherland in December 1999.
</P>
<P>
The preparatory committee will be headed by one chairman and
nine vice-chairmen.  
</P>
</TEXT>
