<HEADLINE> Senior British Spy Arrested in Iran </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, April 26 (Xinhua) -- A high ranking agent of the
British Intelligence Service (MI6) has been arrested in Iran under
charges of illegally filming military areas.
</P>
<P>
Robert Gavin was detained in Iran's western province of
Kurdistan while taking pictures and shooting films of military
establishments, Iran's morning daily Jomhuri Islami Sunday quoted
an informed source as saying.
</P>
<P>
The unnamed source said that Gavin, holding a tourist visa,
entered the military areas without any permission as a reporter of
the British Broadcasting Corporation (BBC).
</P>
<P>
The MI6 agent has been in detention for a week for questioning
and he has confessed to his spying activities in Iran and several
Arab countries, the source said. However, no Iranian authorities
have confirmed the arrest.
</P>
<P>
Some Arab diplomats and reporters here described Gavin's
activities as "suspicious," saying that BBC has screened several
films made by the Briton from prohibited and sensitive military
areas in Arab countries.
</P>
<P>
It was not known how he has managed to shoot the films, but an
Arab diplomat said it is likely that the British military attaches
in the Persian Gulf region filmed the establishments and passed
them on to Gavin.
</P>
<P>
One Arab diplomat, whose name was not given, also said that
Gavin had been willing to pay huge sums of money in return for
military information from Arab reporters, but the Arabs refrained
from cooperating with him. 
</P>
</TEXT>
