<HEADLINE> 31 Kurdish Rebels Killed in Southeastern Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, April 26 (Xinhua) -- A total of 31 members of the
outlawed Kurdish Workers' Party (PKK) were killed in military
operations staged by the Turkish security forces in southeastern
Turkey over the past two days.
</P>
<P>
A statement issued by the office of Emergency Regional Rule
Sunday said that the government troops had wiped out 26 PKK
militants, wounded one and captured four others in clashes with
the PKK in the provinces of Diyarbakir, Bingol, Mus and Bitlis.
</P>
<P>
However, the statement said that three soldiers of the
security forces were also killed in the clashes.
</P>
<P>
The security forces killed five PKK rebels and wounded three in
Kayabogazi village in Catak town of Van province linking
neighboring Iran on Saturday, added the statement.
</P>
<P>
Turkish Chief of General Staff Ismail Hakki Karadayi has said
that 95 percent of the PKK rebels have been annihilated in
government troops' military operations in both southeastern Turkey
and northern Iraq.
</P>
<P>
More than 35,000 soldiers, rebels and civilians were killed in
armed clashes since the Kurdish group launched the bloody war for
the independent "Republic of Kurdistan" against the Turkish
government. 
</P>
