<HEADLINE> Russian LDPR Re-elects Zhirinovsky as Party Leader </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, April 26 (Xinhua) -- Vladimir Zhirinovsky was
re-elected leader of the Liberal Democratic Party of Russia (LDPR)
at the party's eighth congress here on Saturday, the Interfax news
agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Zhirinovsky is to head the party for at least another six
years, according to the report. The party's congress was attended
by 1,262 delegates from across Russia.
</P>
<P>
The congress also elected the party's Supreme Council, which
consists of 15 members headed by Zhirinovsky.
</P>
<P>
The LDPR voted in favor of Sergei Kiriyenko on the third vote
on his premiership in the State Duma on Friday. Kiriyenko was
approved by the Duma as the Russian premier and then appointed by
the president.
</P>
<P>
Our Home is Russia movement on Saturday also concluded its
fifth congress, at which its leader, former Prime Minister Viktor
Chernomyrdin, reaffirmed his intention to run for the presidency
in the year 2000.
</P>
<P>
Our Home is Russia faction also voted for Kiriyenko as premier
of the country in the third round of vote in Duma on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Chernomyrdin stressed that Our Home is Russia "does not join
the opposition to either the president or the government", as it
cannot be in opposition to "its own cause -- the cause of the
rebirth of Russia." 
</P>
