<HEADLINE> Cyclone Kills Eight People in French Polynesia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, April 26 (Xinhua) -- French President Jacques Chirac
Sunday expressed his sorrow for the eight people killed when a
tropical cyclone struck Iles-sous-Le Vent in the French Polynesian
islands in the South Pacific on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Apart from the eight deaths, one person was missing and 20
others were injured when the cyclone "Depression Alan" swept
across the islands, according to media reports here.
</P>
<P>
On the island of Tahaa, a man and his two children, a young
mother and a baby were killed, while the bodies of three others
were found in ruins of houses knocked down by the cyclone on the
island of Raiatea, said rescuers.
</P>
<P>
Police and other rescuers are looking for more victims in
ruins, while all the injured have been rushed to hospital in the
nearby island of Papeete.
</P>
<P>
Local schools, churches and public buildings are sheltering
people who have left their houses in fear of more attacks from
the cyclone.
</P>
<P>
The official weather forecasting institution Meteo France said
the islands of Tahiti and Morea in the Polynesia would be hit by
more storms on Sunday. 
</P>
