<HEADLINE> Chinese Vice-President Starts Visit to South Korea </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, April 26 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-President Hu Jintao
arrived here on Sunday afternoon for a five-day official visit to
South Korea.
</P>
<P>
In a written statement upon his arrival, Hu said his current
visit is aimed at making friends, deepening understanding and
enhancing trust between the two countries and peoples.
</P>
<P>
Hu, a member of the Standing Committee of the Political Bureau
of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of China, said the
further development of friendly and cooperative relations between
China and South Korea will not only serve the basic interest of
the two peoples, but are also conducive to peace, stability and
development in Asia and the world as a whole.
</P>
<P>
Hu said that he will make extensive contacts with South Korean
leaders and people from all walks of life and have in-depth
exchange of views over issues of common concern with them to push
forward a long term, good-neighborly and cooperative ties oriented
to the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
During his visit, Hu is expected to meet South Korean President
Kim Dae-jung and Acting Prime Minister Kim Jong-pil and leaders of
parliament and political parties.
</P>
<P>
South Korea is the second leg of Hu's East Asia tour. He is
also expected to visit Ulsan and Cheju apart from Seoul.
</P>
<P>
