<HEADLINE> French PM Calls Slavery "Infamy" </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, April 26 (Xinhua) -- French Prime Minister Lionel Jospin
 Sunday said that slavery, which was once run by Europeans in
their American colonies but has well survived by the end of the
20th century in different forms around the world, is an "infamy"
of humanity.
</P>
<P>
"Always built on the same denial of humanity, slavery has not
disappeared," said Jospin in an interview with the daily "East
Republicain" published in Haute Saone in east France.
</P>
<P>
Jospin will go to Champagney, Haute Saone, on Monday to
commemorate the 150th anniversary of the abolition of slavery by
France in its colonies in America.
</P>
<P>
While calling for vigilance against slavery, Jospin said that
France will continue to fight for the eradication of this infamy in
the world. 
</P>
