<HEADLINE> Tibet Power Industry Witnesses Rapid Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LHASA, April 26 (Xinhua) -- Southwest China's Tibet Autonomous
Region raised its installed power generation capacity by 93,500 kw
to 300,000 kw during 1997, with the increase significantly
alleviating serious power shortages.
</P>
<P>
Tibet generated 600 million kilowatt hours of electricity
during the year and basically fulfilled the needs of both economic
development and private consumption, according to an official with
the region's power bureau.
</P>
<P>
The region spent 600 million yuan on power industry last year.
</P>
<P>
The official noted that last September's completion of the four
generating units at the Yanghu Power Station ended Lhasa's history
of frequent blackouts.
</P>
<P>
The rapid growth of Tibet's power industry is part of the local
government's bid to accelerate the construction of infrastructure
needed to attract both domestic and foreign investors. 
</P>
