<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Children Can Be Susceptible to Hypertension </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, April 26 (Xinhua) -- Nigerians medical experts have
warned that children blood pressure should be measured regularly
as they too could be susceptible to hypertension.
</P>
<P>
The members of the Nigerian Hypertension Society (NHS) at
their sixth annual scientific and general meeting held here over
the weekend revealed that hypertension has been found in many
children, disproving the old theory that hypertension is an adult
disease.
</P>
<P>
According to NHS Secretary Ambrose Isah, research findings had
shown that hypertension does not start in the elderly rather
people grow with it.
</P>
<P>
Some 10-12 percent of the populace are affected with ailment
which has been described as a silent killer because of damage it
does to body organs even in the absence of obvious symptoms, he
said.
</P>
<P>
A medical director of a western Nigerian clinic, who delivered
the lecture, said he had found 6,000 children in a research he
conducted across the globe.
</P>
<P>
The children with the exception of one were below the age of
nine, he said the Guardian reported Sunday.
</P>
<P>
In one research last year, he said, hypertension was found in
some children at the age of 0-18 years, an evidence that calls
for regular measure of children blood pressure.
</P>
<P>
According to them, growing with hypertension, which is
natural, still assumes an epidemic proportion especially among
the black population and the only solution to the ailment is to
tackle both the primary and secondary problem before it becomes
complicated.
</P>
<P>
He appealed to the government to establish a center where
public education can be given to people on hypertension as well
as provide regular check up of blood pressure. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
