<HEADLINE> WB Aids Uganda in Districts Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, April 26 (Xinhua) -- World Bank has allocated 400
million Ugandan Shillings (400,000 U.S. Dollars) to develop four
districts in the country.
</P>
<P>
The money will be released in two instalments of equal
amounts, with the first part of the fund already handed over to
the project management units in the ministry of local
governments, The Monitor paper reported Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The projects to be covered include access roads, drainage,
sanitation and water supply in Kabarole, Masaka, Mbale and Lira.
</P>
<P>
These four, the report added, were picked as pilot schemes and
when they pass the test, other districts will surely benefit.
</P>
</TEXT>
