<HEADLINE> China Sets Up Market Information System On Internet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, April 26 (Xinhua) -- China is set to establish an
export information system on internet, introducing the country's
famous and fine export products, said an official with the
Ministry of Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation (Moftec).
</P>
<P>
According to Zhang Daming, deputy-director of Office of
Information Leading Group of Moftec, software designing for the
internet information system titled "Products Made in China" is
under construction.
</P>
<P>
It will be developed as the world's largest export products
transaction center by taking advantage of internet, which has so
far aroused strong reaction from industrial and commercial
enterprises nationwide, said the official.
</P>
<P>
The move is designed to blaze new trails in an effort to boost
the country's import and export trade by fully utilizing the
modern information network technology, he added.
</P>
<P>
The internet information system "Products Made in China" will
involve all the country's prestigious enterprises and their
products, which will be available for consultation to all the
government institutions, commercial groups and enterprises across
the world. 
