<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 400 Chinese Cities Implement Living Standard Guarantee System </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 26 (Xinhua) -- A total of 400 Chinese cities
have established a subsistence living standard guarantee system,
according to an official meeting held here.
</P>
<P>
As a result, 2.25 million urban Chinese residents with living
difficulties have obtained relief and other assistance.
</P>
<P>
Meeting sources said that the subsistence living standard
guarantee system will be spread nationwide next year, with some
six million people expected to benefit from the scheme.
</P>
<P>
The minimum standard of living guarantee system has served as
an effective "shock absorber" for social stability in Shanghai,
where the system was first implemented five years ago, a municipal
official told the meeting.
</P>
<P>
The four-day meeting was attended by representatives from
China's four municipalities, which are Beijing, Shanghai, Tianjin
and Chongqing.
</P>
<P>
China has more than 600 cities altogether. 
</P>
</TEXT>
