<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shantou Reports Rapid Growth in Telecommunications Sector </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANTOU, April 26 (Xinhua) -- The telecommunications sector of
Shantou, a special economic zone in south China's Guangdong
Province, experienced rapid growth in recent years.
</P>
<P>
The telephone switchboard capacity of urban Shantou reached
445,000 lines by the end of last year, with the number of
installed telephones up from 180,000 in 1993 to 338,000 last year,
according to official statistics.
</P>
<P>
Currently, 99 percent of all households in Shantou have
installed telephones.
</P>
<P>
Shantou's number of new mobile phone users was 30,676 last
year, an increase of 9,986 over 1996. In another analysis, there
are eight mobile phones per 100 families on average.
</P>
<P>
Official statistics also show that Shantou's posts and
telecommunications business volume was valued at 1.26 billion yuan
in 1997, up from 420 million yuan in 1993.
</P>
<P>
An official survey indicates that annual per capita spending on
telecommunications soared an average 32 percent in Shantou between
1993 and 1997, with the per person amount hitting 275.9 yuan in
1997, a surge of 42.5 percent from the previous year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
