<HEADLINE> Maldivian President to Visit Bangladesh </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, April 26 (Xinhua) -- Maldivian President Maumoon Abdul
Gayoom will arrive here next Wednesday on a three-day visit to
Bangladesh, official sources said Sunday.
</P>
<P>
During his stay here, Gayoom, who is the current chairman of
the South Asian Association for Regional Cooperation (SAARC), will
hold official talks with Prime Minister Sheikh Hasina on bilateral
relations, and regional and international issues and activities of
SAARC.
</P>
<P>
Gayoom will also meet his Bangladeshi counterpart Shahabuddin
Ahmed, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
This will be Gayoom's first visit to Bangladesh after he
assumed the chairmanship of SAARC at its 9th summit in Male, the
Maldives, last May. 
</P>
