<HEADLINE> Yunnan Airlines To Open Kunming-Fukuoka Flight </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, April 26 (Xinhua) -- Yunnan Airlines, based in
Kunming, capital city of southwest Yunnan Province, plans to open
an international chartered passenger flight between Kunming and
Fukuoka, Japan, on May 1.
</P>
<P>
The chartered flight will be turned into a regular one in
future, according to Yunnan Airlines sources.
</P>
<P>
The 2,927 km-flight takes three hours and 50 minutes and will
use a Boeing 737-300.
</P>
<P>
Yunnan is the one of the most scenic provinces in China, with
local residents from 26 ethnic groups.
</P>
<P>
In 1997, 750,000 overseas tourists, including nearly 50,000
Japanese, visited the province, which ranks sixth among all
provinces.
</P>
<P>
With the opening of the new flight, Yunnan Airlines will
operate nine international flights. All the eight existing flights
fly to Southeast Asian countries and regions. 
</P>
</TEXT>
