<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka's Navy Seizes 17 Kilos of Heroin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, April 26 (Xinhua) -- The Sri Lanka navy seized 17
kilograms of heroin Saturday from a boat in Negombo lagoon, 35 km
from Colombo, the Sunday Observer newspaper reported.
</P>
<P>
One suspect was arrested along with the contraband, but two
others aboard the boat jumped into the sea and escaped.
</P>
<P>
The navy said at least three boats were involved in the
smuggling and a bigger quantity of heroin could be in the other
boats.
</P>
<P>
The seizure was handed over to local police.
</P>
<P>
It is the largest drug smuggling case in Sri Lanka this year,
and is also the third largest haul of drugs in the island country.
</P>
<P>
The biggest seizure of heroin was made in 1989 at Colombo
Airport where a Nigerian national was arrested with 29 kilos of
heroin.
</P>
<P>
The drugs may have been originating from Afghanistan. Drug
smugglers usually purchase the contraband goods in Pakistan and
transport them by boat to Sri Lanka from South India. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
