<DOCNO> XIE19980426.0122 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Afghan Factions to Start Crucial Talks Sunday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, April 26 (Xinhua) -- Afghanistan's Taliban militia
and the rival Northern Alliance will begin on Sunday their first
formal face-to-face meeting in more than a year, with an aim to
negotiate an early end to the protracted conflict ravaging their
homeland.
</P>
<P>
The Joint Steering Committee, which is made up of five
delegates from the Taliban and nine from the alliance, is to meet
at 10. a.m. (local time) at the Punjab House near the National
Assembly in Islamabad.
</P>
<P>
The meeting is being jointly sponsored by the United Nations
and the Organization of the Islamic Conference.
</P>
<P>
The two sides have already agreed on a tentative agenda,
designed to achieve an ultimate objective of establishing peace
and forming a broadbased government in their homeland, a spokesman
for the Pakistani Foreign Office said Saturday.
</P>
<P>
After holding a ceremonial meeting, the rival factions would
immediately proceed to working sessions, and they would first
formally adopt the agenda, which "at the moment is a secret
agenda," the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
It is believed that the agenda may include the establishment of
a Ulema Commission, ceasefire, exchange of prisoners of war and
provision of aid to the Afghan people.
</P>
<P>
On the duration of the meeting, he said, it depends on the
process of the talks. Both sides will assess the situation on the
basis of progress, and will move forward accordingly, the
spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
The Taliban militia now control about two thirds of
Afghanistan, including the capital Kabul, and have imposed a
strict Islamic rule on a country gripped by 20 years of civil war.
</P>
<P>
The Northern Alliance, which controls the rest of the country,
consists of the ousted Afghan president Burhannudin Rabbani,
former Afghan military chief Ahmad Masood, ethnic Uzbek warlord
Rashid Dostum and a Shiite Muslim faction. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
