<HEADLINE> Chinese Vice-President Leaves Osaka For Seoul </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OSAKA, Japan, April 26 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-President Hu
Jintao, winding up his six-day tour of Japan, left here for Seoul
on Sunday afternoon for an official visit to South Korea.
</P>
<P>
During his stay in Tokyo, Hu held talks with Japanese Prime
Minister Ryutaro Hashimoto, and met with heads of major Japanese
political parties and business leaders.
</P>
<P>
Before leaving Tokyo for Kyoto on a tour to western Japan on
Friday, Hu told a press conference that he was satisfied with the
results of his visit, citing that he had reached consensus on a
series of major issues with Japanese leaders.
</P>
<P>
South Korea is the second leg of Hu's two-nation tour, his first
overseas trip after assuming vice-presidency last month. 
