<HEADLINE> Pakistan PM Returns From Visit to Italy, Belgium </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, April 26 (Xinhua) -- Pakistani Prime Minister Nawaz
Sharif, who arrived back Saturday night from a week-long tour of
Italy and Belgium, said his visit was highly successful and would
further improve economic and commercial ties with the two West
European countries.
</P>
<P>
Pakistan enjoys cordial relations with Italy and Belgium,
particularly in the field of trade and commerce, and his visit
would largely help in attracting foreign investment, Sharif told
reporters at the airport of Lahore, capital of Punjab province,
the official Associated Press of Pakistan reported.
</P>
<P>
He said the talks with his counterparts of the two countries
focused on improving bilateral economic and commercial ties.
</P>
<P>
He said Italian and Belgian businessmen had expressed a keen
interest in investing in various sectors in Pakistan. 
</P>
