<DOCNO> XIE19980426.0131 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Thai PM Backs Crackdown on Corrupt Policemen </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, April 26 (Xinhua) -- Thai Prime Minister Chuan Leekpai
has voiced support for efforts to purge senior traffic police
officers who allegedly order their subordinates to extort cash
from motorists.
</P>
<P>
"No policemen, senior or junior, will be spared if there is
evidence pointing to their involvement (in the extortion)," the
prime minister said in remarks published by Sunday's Nation
newspaper.
</P>
<P>
Chuan was commenting on the case of a group of junior
expressway traffic policemen who last week told the ITV television
news station that they were forced by their superiors to extort
cash from motorists.
</P>
<P>
The exposure came after the station aired footage showing
policemen at an expressway toll gate taking money from motorists
they had pulled over.
</P>
<P>
The allegations prompted the Interior Ministry and the Police
Department to threaten a purge of police officers involved in the
scandal.
</P>
<P>
Chuan described the problem as a case of chronic bad moral
values among certain people and said it would take time to correct
this.
</P>
<P>
"People should not tolerate something like this, and we have to
be serious in trying to correct it," he said.
</P>
<P>
Interior Minister Sanan Kachornprasart said Saturday that he
had ordered the national police chief to take drastic action
against any officers involved in the scandal.
</P>
<P>
Sanan said he also planned to discuss with Bangkok Governor
Bhichit Rattakul the possibility of canceling the traffic
regulation that entitles police who arrest law-breaking motorists
to a cash reward derived from fines imposed on offenders, since
the practice appeared to favor extortion.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, a police officer, accused by his subordinates of
having ordered them to extort cash from motorists, denied all
allegations and said they had been fabricated by some policemen
whom he had transferred.
</P>
<P>
"The accusations are false. they just want to take revenge
after I ordered some policemen to be transferred for extorting
cash from motorists on the expressway on march 17," he said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
