<HEADLINE> Cabinet Reshuffle Ends in Albania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, April 25 (Xinhua) -- The 12-day-long cabinet reshuffle
in Albania concluded Wednesday with the approval of Edi Rama as
minister of culture, youth and sports by President Rexhep Meidani.
</P>
<P>
The number of the cabinet members has been reduced to 18 from
22 with the dismissal of eight and the recruitment of
four. Meanwhile, some officials shifted their positions.
</P>
<P>
In the new cabinet, Fatos Nano remains as prime minister while
Bashkim Fino becomes deputy prime minister and minister for local
authorities. Kastriot Islami, former state minister under direct
control of the prime minister, becomes another deputy prime
minister and minister of coordination.
</P>
<P>
Four new cabinet members are Luan Hajdaraga, defense minister,
Anastas Angjeli, minister of labor and social affairs, Edi Rama,
minister of culture, youth and sports, and Ilir Meta, state
secretary for the European integration.
</P>
<P>
Ministers of foreign affairs, justice, finance, economy and
privatization, agriculture and food, public works and transport,
education and science remain in their office.
</P>
<P>
The aim of the reshuffle is to simplify the government
structure, improve the coordination among government organs, and
strengthen the government's efforts to fight against corruption
and social crimes and to revive the economy.
</P>
<P>
The reshuffle began on April 14 when the ruling five coalition
parties reached an agreement on restructuring the government.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
