On the same day in 1945, 250,000 people in northern Italy
joined an insurrection launched by the resistance movement,
successfully liberating more than 100 cities including Milan from
the rule of Fascists.
</P>
<P>
Fascist dictator Benito Mussolini was captured and executed on
April 28, 1945. 
