<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Eggplant Tree Popular in Northeastern Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, April 26 (Xinhua) -- An imported variety of eggplant
"trees" is being grown widely in Liaoyang, in northeast China's
Liaoning Province.
</P>
<P>
The trees are a grafted variety imported from Japan and tested
on a small plot in Liaoyang City in 1990.
</P>
<P>
The eggplant trees have an average height of two meters. Each
bears 30 fruit with the maximum of 50 and has an output of 10
kilograms, three times the output for an ordinary eggplant.
</P>
<P>
In this way, farmers can net an output value of 300,000 yuan
from a hectare of hothouse eggplant fields.
</P>
<P>
So far, the eggplant trees are grown on 2,000 hectares of land,
or 70 percent of the greenhouse grown eggplant in Liaoyang. In
Liaoning Province, the new variety has been sown on 8,933 hectares
of land.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
