<HEADLINE> Ticktes for Five More World Cup Matches Sold out </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, April 25 (Xinhua) -- Five more matches at the World Cup
later this year are sold out following Saturday's fourth day of
telephone sales, local reports said here on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
About 41,000 of the original 110,000 tickets for sale are still
left but 12 matches of the 55 offered by the organizers are
completely sold out.
</P>
<P>
Bruno Travade, the committee's director of communication, said
about 15,000 tickets had been sold during Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The five matches which are sold out are: Argentina vs Japan on
June 14 in Toulouse, Brazil vs Morocco on June 16 in Nantes,
Argentina vs Jamaica on June 21 in the Parc des Princes, France vs
Denmark on June 24 in Lyon and Colombia vs England on June 26 in
Lens.
</P>
<P>
