<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Echoes From Mercosur </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MONTEVIDEO, April 25 (Xinhua) -- Here are major news in
the Southern Common Market (Mercosur) countries:

Argentine Senate Passes Law on Malvinas
</P>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES -- The Argentine Senate on Wednesday approved a
draft law that proposes to punish national or foreign firms
which take part in any form of exploitation in the Malvinas
(Falkland) Islands without the government authorization.
</P>
<P>
The law stipulates that any concession or exploitation of
minerals in the Malvinas must get a previous permission from the
Argentine government.
</P>
<P>
It also says that the national or foreign firms which violate
this law will not be allowed to realize any act of commerce in
the Argentine territory.

Brazilian Monetary Reserves Surpasses 70 Billion U.S. dollars
</P>
<P>
BRASILIA -- Brazilian hard currency reserves amounted to 72.5
billion dollars by the middle of this month, according to the
Central Bank of this country.
</P>
<P>
Before the Asian crisis, the Brazilian monetary reserves were
63 billion dollars and it dropped to 52 billion dollars at the end of
last year.
</P>
<P>
The figure could reach 80 billion dollars soon, the central
bank said.

Argentina, Guatemala Sign Cooperation Agreements
</P>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES -- Argentina and Guatemala on Tuesday signed two
agreements on animal and vegetal health and on exemption of visas
for official passports.
</P>
<P>
The agreement on animal health proposes to exchange information
and technology between the two countries for the trade of animals.

Brazilian Soybean to Have Record Harvest
</P>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO -- The Brazilian soybean harvest will reach a
record this year of more than 30 million tons, according to the
Brazilian press.
</P>
<P>
It is estimated that Brazil will export soybeans in grain and
byproducts worth five billion to 5.3 billions dollars.

Motor Vehicle Imports in Brazil in First Quarter
</P>
<P>
BRASILIA -- Vehicle imports in Brazil totalled 144
million dollars in the first quarter of this year, 32.6 percent
more than in the same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
The Finance Ministry said that this increase was promoted by
the devaluation of the Asian currencies, especially the Japanese
yen.
</P>
<P>
Sources from motor vehicle manufacturing sector said that
Brazil will invest 20 billion dollars to build new plants, which
could provide 10,000 new jobs.

Rains To Cause Mercosur Big Losses in Rice Harvest
</P>
<P>
MONTEVIDEO -- Mercosur countries will lose 600,000 tons of rice
because of the recent rains, according to a report here.
</P>
<P>
Brazil will lose 300,000 tons, Argentina will lose 200,000 tons
and Uruguay will lose 100,000 tons, the report said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
