<HEADLINE> Czech Police Seize 120 Kilograms of Drugs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PRAGUE, April 25 (Xinhua) -- The Czech police and customs have
seized 120 kilograms of heroin and arrested a number of drug
trafficking suspects in a recent anti-drug campaign.
</P>
<P>
This was disclosed by Jiri Komorous, director of the Czech
anti-narcotics center on Friday.
</P>
<P>
He said the seized drugs had a street value of 290 million
Czech korun (about 8.8 million U.S. dollars) and the suspects were
now under custody.
</P>
<P>
In recent years drug traffickers have plunged this central
European nation into a trading center by taking advantage of its
easy connections to other countries.
</P>
<P>
With increased influx of drugs, drug abusers, especially among
the youth, have soared in number. It is reported that in the age
group of 14 to 18, drug taking rate reaches 41.2 percent,
with Prague leading the nation at 52.5 percent. 
</P>
