<HEADLINE> Venezuela Backs Cuba in Joining Regional Blocs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CARACAS, April 25 (Xinhua) -- Venezuela backs Cuba in joining
the regional organizations, said Miguel Angel Burelli, foreign
minister of Venezuela Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The diplomatic line of Venezuela is similar to that expressed
by President Rafael Caldera of Chile, said Burelli.
</P>
<P>
On Cuba's return to the Organization of American States (OAS),
Caldera said Venezuela backed Cuba if it wanted to do it.
</P>
<P>
Cuba, suspended from the 34-member OAS in 1959, has said that
it will only return to the organization on its own terms.
</P>
<P>
Cuba, an observer of the Latin American Integration
Association, is also seeking membership of the organization
composed of 11 countries including Venezuela. 
