<P>
YANGON, April 26 (Xinhua) -- Myanmar and India will cooperate
in the agricultural sector as part of their efforts to promote
economic cooperation and bilateral ties between the two countries,
the New Light of Myanmar newspaper said on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Under a memorandum of understanding reached Saturday between
Myanmar Minister of Agriculture and Irrigation Major-General Nyunt
Tin and his visiting Indian counterpart Som Pal, the two countries
