</P>
<P>
-- Some 2.27 million rural people in Xinyang Prefecture, Henan
Province, have bid farewell to poverty in the last 15 years, with
per capita annual income reaching 1,589 yuan in 1997, about
sixfold of the 1983 figure. Currently, Xinyang still has 300,000
poverty-stricken people in the rural area.
</P>
<P>
-- A subsistence living standard guarantee system has been
established in 400 Chinese cities since last September. The number
accounts for two thirds of all Chinese cities.
</P>
<P>
-- A lengthy article extolled China's statistical work but at
the same time urged official statistics to be "more accurate, more
rapid, and more comprehensive".
</P>
<P>
"Xinhua Daily Telegraph"
</P>
<P>
-- The rural population of northeast China's Heilongjiang
Province dropped to 17.29 million by the end of last year, while
the province's urban population rose to 20.22
million. Heilongjiang has thus become China's first agricultural
powerhouse whose rural population is smaller than urban population.
</P>
<P>
-- The marketing and distribution system of east China's
Jiangsu Province has cut its payroll of administrative personnel
by more than 50 percent over the recent years. The system's
commodity turnover totaled 221.3 billion yuan-worth last year,
about one fifth of the national figure.
</P>
<P>
"Beijing Daily"
</P>
<P>
-- China's largest retail book shop, Beijing Book Mansion, is
expected to open for business next month.
</P>
<P>
