out Saturday for a mass campaign to clean the city's streets and
green land.
</P>
<P>
-- More than 2,000 displaced workers in Beijing's suburban
Shunyi County have found new jobs, thanks to the help from the
local industrial and commercial bureau.
</P>
<P>
"China Daily"
</P>
<P>
-- China's new Minister of Agriculture, Chen Yaobang, vowed to
strengthen the country's agricultural sector through a practical
approach, saying that the key task of his ministry in coming years
is to focus on farmland capital construction.
</P>
<P>
-- Officials of the State Administration of Taxation said that
fees charged by local governments to fund the development of
public facilities would be brought within the ambit of the
national taxation system as part of China's review of the
off-budget levies. Those fees to be turned into taxes are likely
to be charges applied on an ongoing basis, such as those relating
to environmental protection and social security.
</P>
<P>
-- China recently slashed its massive stockpile of cotton by
selling more than one million bales (about 218,000 tons) on the
international market. If possible, China will sell more cotton.
</P>
<P>
-- Chinese auditors will sharpen their vigilance over State
finances and State property and will step up their fight against
corruption, according to newly appointed Auditor General Li
Jinhua. Li said that auditors will be required not only to check
the authenticity of fiscal income and expenditure claims, but also
to make suggestions and give advice on how to strengthen
management and improve efficiency. 
</P>
