<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Development Zone Announces Tax Breaks to Attract Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, April 26 (Xinhua) -- A national high-tech development
zone in Nanning, capital of Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region, has
announced tax breaks to attract domestic and overseas investment.
</P>
<P>
Located two kilometers from the downtown area, the
28-square-kilometer development zone has already drawn 270
enterprises since 1992. The zone houses a science-and-industry
park, an agro-biological engineering demonstration area, a bonded
warehouse area and a science-and-technology street.
</P>
<P>
According to new policies, large-scale high-tech development in
the zone is entitled to rebates on income and value-added taxes
during its loan period. The rebates are to be used for debt
service.
</P>
<P>
The authorized enterprises may also get approval from the
zone's management committee for income tax rebates for two years
from its date of operation.
</P>
<P>
Infrastructure and high-tech projects may also enjoy exemption
and reduction of urban construction fees as well as lower land
payments with the approval of the city government.
</P>
<P>
Enterprises involved in infrastructure and service trade with
an operation term of more than 10 years may receive tax rebates
within two years of its date of operation in the zone.
</P>
<P>
The enterprises with investment and technology from outside
Nanning are entitled to the above preferential terms along with
foreign-funded enterprises. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
