<HEADLINE> Doherty On Course for Second Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, April 25 (Xinhua) -- Defending champion Ken Doherty
earned a quarter-final place with a second round win over
England's Stephen Lee in the World Snooker Championships in
Sheffield on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
But the Irishman, who included a 137 break in his 13-8 win,
acknowledged he faced a real fight to keep his title.
</P>
<P>
Welshman Mark Williams could well be one of those challengers
after completing an impressive 13-6 win over six-times world
champion Steve Davis to join Doherty in the last eight.
</P>
<P>
In-form Londoner Jimmy White, who knocked out favourite
Scotland's Stephen Hendry in the first round, ended the first
session of his match against Darren Morgan with a four-frame lead.
</P>
<P>
Former winner John Parrott also booked a quarter-final clash
with fellow Briton John Higgins after defeating Malta's Tony
Drago.
</P>
<P>
Britain's Peter Ebdon compiled two century breaks on his way
to a 5-3 lead over Fergal O'Brien of Ireland.  
</P>
</TEXT>
