<HEADLINE> Chang, Courier Reach Final in Florida </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 25 (Xinhua) -- Top-seed Michael Chang beat
Sweden's Mikael Tillstrom while third-seed Jim Courier defeated
Romanian Andrei Pavel to advance to the final of the U.S. Men's
Clay Court Championship in Orlando, Florida on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The defending champion Chang, whose world ranking has dropped
from second to 12th after suffering 11 early-round defeats since
winning this tournament last year, cruised to a 6-3, 6-4 victory.
</P>
<P>
Former number one Courier lost the first set 4-6, came back to
take the second set 6-3 and broke Pavel in the fifth and seventh
games of the third set to win it 6-2.
</P>
<P>
Chang has an 11-10 lead in career matchups between the two, and
has won five of their last six encounters. In their only previous
meeting on clay, Courier won in three sets in the Italian Open in
1993.
</P>
<P>
Courier, ranked 57th in the world, reached his first final
since winning the China Open in Beijing last October, one of three
titles he won in 1997.
</P>
<P>
Courier has won 22 singles titles, including back-to-back
French Opens in 1991-92 and consecutive Australian Opens in
1992-93. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
