<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Calzaghe Retains WBO Super-middleweight Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, April 25 (Xinhua) -- Welshman Joe Calzaghe retained his
World Boxing Organization (WBO) super-middleweight title after
beating veteran Paraguayan challenger Juan Carlos Gimenez in a
bout held in Cardiff on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Calzaghe dominated the bout from the first round, continually
cornering the challenger although he was not able to knock down
his opponent.
</P>
<P>
Calzaghe continued the attack in the later rounds and rarely
got hit by Gimenez. By the end of the 10-round bout, Calzaghe
retained his title with a decision.
</P>
<P>
It was Calzaghe's second defense of the title he won by
outpointing veteran Chris Eubank in October last year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
