<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jaermann Wins Amstel Gold World Cup Cycling Race </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, April 25 (Xinhua) -- Swiss veteran Rolf Jaermann
edged Dutchman Maarten den Bakker in a two-man sprint finish to
win the Amstel Gold World Cup cycling race in Maastricht,
Netherlands, on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Jaermann, 32, who also won the race in 1993, beat den Bakker
by a wheel at the end of the 257 kilometers race with a time of
six hours 43 minutes and 20 seconds.
</P>
<P>
Italian Michele Bartoli, winner of Liege-Bastogne-Liege World
Cup race last week, took third place with 21 seconds behind, ahead
of Dutch champion Michael Boogerd and Dane Bo Hamburger.
</P>
<P>
World Cup holder Bartoli also retained the lead in the overall
standings after the fifth World Cup stage in the 10-race series.
</P>
<P>
The competition now takes a break until the San Sebastian
classic race in Spain on August 8.  
</P>
</TEXT>
